<BaseLayout title="Halloween — Unmasking the Holidays — Nazaryah" description="Halloween is the ancient Celtic festival of Samhain — dedicated to death, the spirit world, and communion with the dead. Every element is an abomination per Deuteronomy 18.">
  <div class="hol-wrap">
    <section class="hol-hero">
      <p class="hol-series">&#8213; Unmasking the Holidays · October &#8213;</p>
      <h1 class="hol-title">Halloween</h1>
      <p class="hol-sub">20 Traditions. A death festival. The one holiday that never pretended to be Christian.</p>
    </section>
    <section class="hol-section">
      <div class="hol-prose">
        <p>Halloween (October 31st) is the ancient Celtic festival of Samhain — a night dedicated to death, the spirit world, and communion with the dead. It marks the Celtic new year, when the sun god's power waned and the veil between the living and the dead was believed to be at its thinnest. Bonfires were lit to strengthen the dying sun and ward off evil spirits.</p>
        <p>It is the one holiday that doesn't even pretend to be Christian. Every element — costumes (disguising oneself from spirits), jack-o'-lanterns (carved to repel the dead), trick-or-treating (offerings left to appease wandering spirits), bonfires, witches, divination — traces directly to Celtic death and spirit-worship practices that Yahuah explicitly condemns.</p>
        <p>Deuteronomy 18:10–12 lists the practices Yahuah calls abominations: "There shall not be found among you anyone who... uses divination, or is an observer of times, or an enchanter, or a witch, or a charmer, or a consulter with familiar spirits, or a wizard, or a necromancer." Halloween is the one day each year when all of these are celebrated culturally — including by the church. This study examines 20 Halloween traditions, tracing every element back to Samhain.</p>
      </div>
    </section>
    <section class="hol-coming">
      <div class="hol-coming-inner">
        <div class="hol-coming-icon">&#9685;</div>
        <h2 class="hol-coming-title">Full Study Coming</h2>
        <p>This study is being assembled. Return to the <a href="/holidays" class="hol-link">Holidays hub</a> or explore <a href="/sun-worship/sacred-act" class="hol-link">The Sacred Act</a> while this page is built.</p>
      </div>
    </section>
    <div class="hol-nav">
      <a href="/holidays/easter" class="hol-nav-link">&#8592; Easter</a>
      <a href="/holidays/christmas" class="hol-nav-link">Christmas &#8594;</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
